OL,3,CGeorge Galloway promises to give
OL,4,CLabour and Tories 'good kicking'
OL,6,FIn his first Commons outing since he
OL,7,Ftook his seat, paid tribute to his
OL,8,FLabour predecessor Sir Tony Lloyd,
OL,9,Fbefore promising to give both parties
OL,10,Fa "good kicking".
OL,12,FMr Galloway opened his speech by
OL,13,Ftelling MPs: "As I was saying Madame
OL,14,FDeputy Speaker, even in Parliament you
OL,15,Fcan't be a maiden twice."
