OL,4,CLabour and Tories 'good kicking'
OL,6,FIn his first written parliamentary
OL,7,Fquestion to ministers tabled since his
OL,8,Freturn, the Workers Party MP asked if
OL,9,Fministers would "have discussions with
OL,10,FRoyal Mail on the allocation of the RO
OL,11,Fpostcode to Rochdale", but was told
OL,12,Fthis would be an operational matter
OL,13,Ffor the Royal Mail.
OL,15,FHe also hit out at the Budget, telling
OL,16,Fthe Commons: "Frankly all the spices
OL,17,Fin Rochdale could not give flavour to
OL,18,Fwhat can only be described as a
OL,19,Fnothing burger of a Budget."
